<h2>Day 1 Code 1</h2>
<b>Cascading Style Sheets</b> can be added to HTML documents in 3 ways:

<P><B>Inline</B> - by using the <B>style attribute</B> inside HTML elements<br>
Used to style a inidivual unique html element in the line.</P>

<P><B>Internal</B> - by using a <B>style element</B> in the head section of the html page<br>
Used to define style for a single page. It sets the template for all the elements whose style is defined in the head section<BR>
This style will apply to the elements whenever used in the page's body section.</P>

<P><B>External</B> - by using a <B>link</B> element to link to an external CSS file<BR>
    The external style sheet can be written in any text editor & must be saved with a <B>.css</B> extension. The file must not contain any HTML code.
</P>

